b'' b'mark gregory foster writes (concerning corinthians b'' b' the idea was introduced to me once that the reason paul wanted' b' the corinthians to lay aside money for the collection on the' b' first day of the week was that this was when they received their' b' weekly wages.' b'' b'but the ancient romans did not observe a seven-day week. unless a' b'man was working for a jewish employer, he is unlikely to have been' b'paid on the first day of a seven-day week. nor would a jewish' b'employer have kept his wages over the week-end (see lev dt' b'24:15).' b'' b'yours,' b'james kiefer' 